OL,6,FMiss Knight said Pateman had made a
OL,7,Fprevious threat to set his partner on
OL,8,Ffire and had kept the petrol at his
OL,9,Fproperty, but she did not believe him.
OL,11,FA neighbour confirmed she had
OL,12,Foverheard Pateman threatening to set
OL,13,FMs Marshall "a light" several weeks
OL,14,Fearlier, and a fire reconstruction
OL,15,Fexpert concluded the blaze had been
OL,16,Fdeliberately started using an
OL,17,Faccelerant.
OL,19,FPateman was found at his mother's
OL,20,Fhouse, where he had gone to bed,
OL,21,Fcovered in soot.
OL,1,Woz5~k4{$z%~s1z5jw=hw1         G7/10
